Triggers
Positive Triggers
Use this skill when the user asks for:
Health or wellness blog articles
Search-intent briefs for health topics
SEO titles, meta descriptions, slugs, or outlines for wellness content
Evidence-aware drafts
Wellness FAQs
Internal-link ideas for health sites
Safety-friendly medical wording
Disclaimers for health articles
Responsible CTAs for coaching, wellness, nutrition, fitness, or supplement content
Source plans, claim audits, fact-check checklists, or publication-readiness reviews
Negative Triggers
Do not use this skill for:
Personal medical diagnosis
Prescribing medication, supplements, diet therapy, or treatment
Emergency medical guidance
Legal review of advertising compliance
Creating deceptive health claims
Claims that promise cures, prevention, reversal, or guaranteed outcomes
Non-health SEO content unless health or wellness safety is central
Ambiguous Triggers
If the user asks for "wellness copy," determine whether they need blog/editorial content, landing page conversion copy, social media copy, or clinical guidance. Use the skill for editorial SEO content and safety review; ask or state assumptions when the format is unclear.
